==English==

===Etymology===
From the fact that women in the 1950s usually wore bright shirts and that pink was then a popular color.

===Adjective===
'''pink-collar'''

# Of, relating to, or designated of secondary labor market work, traditionally or most likely done by women; usually used in disparagement.
# Of or relating to predominately female business or college.

